wiki.content: “Nobody Gets Me” works as a promotional single for SZA’s sophomore album, SOS. She teased the song uploading a 30-second snippet of it four days before the project was out and a music video was released the same day as the album on December 9, 2022. It’s a break-up ballad encapsulating her feelings through the last moments of her relationship with her ex-fiancé, who was the only person at the time that she feels truly understood her, she tells HOT 97. “This particular song in entirety is a story about my ex-fiancé and how we went through all these arguments, and we broke up. And when we first broke up it was like terible, and I just felt like I was gonna be doomed to be in hell for the rest of my life because nobody understood me the way he did, and like nobody motivated me the way he did. And he was just, you know, this rock in my life that just no longer exists. And it’s just, like, it was insane. The stories that I tell in that song about our arguments, our specific arguments, like that’s kinda the–. That’s the theme on that. I feel like a lot of people don’t understand me but it’s okay.“ Read more on Last.fm. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.
